   <text>
      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">(Copy ¶ ) ¶ St George, Queensland ¶ 10 Sept. 1881. ¶ The Hon. the Chief Secretary of Victoria ¶ Melbourne ¶  ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">M81.09.10</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From John Skuthorpe to Bryan O'Loghlen</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="">Sammlung Perthes Archiv, </seg>
               <seg style="">SPA ARCH PGM 328</seg>
               <seg style="">, </seg>Forschungsbibliothek Gotha der Universität Erfurt.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Skuthorpe's letter was presumably sent to Gotha by M.</p>
               </note>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">(Copy</hi>
               </seg>)</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">St George, Queensland</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">10 Sept. 1881.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">The Hon. the Chief Secretary of Victoria</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Melbourne</hi>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir —</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I beg to report to you my return here from the Western Country, and to inform you that I have possession of the following relics of the Leichardt-Expedition. Leichardt's and Classan's<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="">Classen?</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> journals, a telescope and a compass. Will you appoint a competent agent to take delivery of them on the following terms?</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>A binding agreement to be entered into between us securing me the payment of £6000 on delivery of the articles named, and protecting me against all claims which may be made against me by any persons interested in the ownership of them. I bind myself to deliver them in St George and to place my services at the disposal of your Government, if required, for the space of six months, without further payment, and to point out all localities connected with the discovery, the grave containing Classan's remains, and give every information and assistance to whoever you think fit to appoint.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Your obedient Servant</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>J. R. Skuthorpe</seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                     <p rend="Footnote"
                        style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>A cutting from the <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Argus</seg>, 20 September 1881, p. 6, of a very similar letter from Skuthorpe to the Prime Minister of NSW, Sir Henry Parkes, signed ‘John Richard Skuthorpe’, is filed with the MS. See also M to E. Behm, 12 October 1881.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
         </div>
